#: ../../authentication_authorization/index.rst:3
msgid "Authentication and Authorization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../authentication_authorization/index.rst:5
msgid ""
"Access to information and actions are dictated by permissions assigned to"
" the user either directly or through groups and roles. ESSArch is "
"designed such that each user has a single account which are reused across"
" multiple organizations (groups) with different roles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../authentication_authorization/index.rst:10
msgid ""
"This means that a single user can have the role admin in one "
"organization, an archivist in another and both in a third."
msgstr ""

#: ../../authentication_authorization/index.rst:13
msgid ""
"ESSArch has no requirement that any specific groups or roles are setup or"
" used in an installation, this is all setup and configured according to "
"the needs that the installation is supposed to meet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../authentication_authorization/index.rst:17
msgid ""
"The permissions available are therefore made in as small building blocks "
"as possible to allow either very small and specific roles to be created "
"but tat the same time create roles that can do everything."
msgstr ""

